Given the difficulties of the Nash equilibrium concept to predict the behavior observed in the experiments, we have proposed two alternative explanations for our observation. The first one is a stationary approach based on the idea of the Rosenthal equilibrium29. In principle, one could claim that the rationality parameter t defining the Rosenthal equilibrium could be dependent on (a) the game itself and (b) the risk/costs involved based on the choices available. Given the game we have and our results, we have found that the parameter \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
